<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-587-459  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 587 459.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DEC Professional  May 1989 v8 n5 p28(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Topic's connectivity scheme: Verity's document-retrieval systemuses SQL bridges for application links. (data base management anddocument retrieval system; Structured Query Language)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Birkhead, Evan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Topic, Verity Inc's text retrieval system, also functions as adocument managing system.andP;  An object-oriented querying tool isused to build topics that describe an area of subjects the userneeds to retrieve.andP;  The search objects are a hierarchical outlinethat describes the subject using topics and subtopics.andP;  A 95percent recall accuracy rate is reported.andP;  As a documentmanagement system, Topic retrieves documents stored as free textin on-line flat files or inside an RDBMS structure and ranks themnumerically by relevance.andP;  Written in C, Topic runs on MS-DOS,Unix and VAX-VMS systems from Sun and Pyramid.andP;  Networks supportedinclude Novell, TOPS, NFS, DECnet, 3Com and NFS.andP;  Topic is CGA andEGA compatible and is available in stand-alone multiuser andnetwork configurations.andP;  An X Window System interface is expected.andO;SQL-based bridges to Verity from Sybase, Informix Software, Oracleand Relational Technology will soon be available and will costabout $2,500.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Verity Inc. (product enhancement)Oracle Corp. (marketing)Sybase Inc. (marketing)Relational Technology Inc. (marketing)Informix Software Inc. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    ORCL; RELY.andO;Product:   Topic (Data base management system) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Data Base Management SystemsDocument Management SystemsData Base LanguagesInformation Storage and RetrievalHierarchical OrganizationMarketing AgreementsEnhancementsProduct DevelopmentText Communication.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>